metadata.name: Elotuzumab 300 mg 1 Injection powder lyophilized for solution

clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Investigated for use treatment in leukemia myeloid

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: An immunoconjugate consisting of the humanized monoclonal antibody huMy9 6 conjugated to the cytotoxic maytansinoid derivative DM4 with potential antineoplastic activity The monoclonal antibody portion of anti CD33 monoclonal antibody DM4 conjugate AVE9633 specifically binds to the cell surface antigen CD33 expressed on myeloid leukemia cells upon internalization the DM4 moiety is released binds tubulin and disrupts microtubule assembly disassembly dynamics resulting in the inhibition of cell division and cell growth in myeloid leukemia cells that express CD33 CD33 is expressed on normal non pluripotent hematopoietic stem cells as well as on myeloid leukemia cells National Cancer Institute Drug Dictionary
